    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="48"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Indonesia/1–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Netherlands</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 9, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. For your info and possible future use if instructed, Dept officials made
                    strong informal representations Jan 8 to Helb, Counselor Neth Emb, to end that
                    his Govt would (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) promptly consider and accept political
                    principles set forth Graham’s 84<note n="1" xml:id="d48fn1">Telegram 22, January
                        6, 5 p. m., <ref target="#pg_62">p. 62</ref>.</note> (repeated Hague in
                        <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 9, Jan 9) and (<hi rend="italic"
                        >b</hi>) indicate promptly to Van Zeeland its approval in <pb facs="0085"
                        n="71" xml:id="pg_71"/> order Van Zeeland throw weight his support to
                    proposals within <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss>. Dept informed personally
                    and confidentially by Helb Jan 9 that strong recommendation to <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> to above effect has been made by Neth
                    Emb.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
